12:57.418 --> 12:59.701
I mean, you talk about saying the quiet part out loud.

12:59.981 --> 13:01.123
What's David thinking?

13:01.944 --> 13:04.307
When all the other boys are invited, accept him.

13:05.308 --> 13:07.251
And so there's some question.

13:07.331 --> 13:09.394
Why was David left out?

13:09.922 --> 13:16.648
And it's possible, of course, that David was certainly the youngest, and therefore he could have been like 10 to 15 years old.

13:17.329 --> 13:20.772
And so maybe it's just that he was just young, and therefore left out.

13:20.792 --> 13:26.938
We know in chapter 17, he's gonna be described by Goliath as a youth, which basically means a child.

13:27.579 --> 13:30.802
He's so young as brothers, go to war, he's not even able to go fight.

13:31.142 --> 13:33.704
So he might just be like, he's like a sixth grade kid.

13:34.465 --> 13:35.826
So it's like, okay, definitely not you.

13:36.047 --> 13:36.647
We're not sure.

13:37.708 --> 13:39.570
But whatever it is, we know he's,

13:39.970 --> 13:42.734
overlooked and underestimated.

13:42.994 --> 13:55.450
There are some, by the way, who when David says he was brought forth in sin and conceived in iniquity, trying to help explain why he was left out, read that not theologically as we typically do, but read it biographically.

13:55.851 --> 13:58.494
Like, could it be that there was some scandal in David's birth?

13:58.534 --> 14:06.404
So David or Jesse rather brings like the real kids, but that other one through that other person, he's out in the field.

14:06.524 --> 14:07.826
