14:42.337 --> 14:46.123
Was there some jealousy that was beginning to creep up?

14:46.143 --> 14:47.565
Was Jesse embarrassed?

14:48.426 --> 14:49.748
I mean, he's like, oh, my bad.

14:49.788 --> 14:50.990
I'm like, I feel terrible.

14:51.050 --> 14:52.232
Here comes the runt of the litter.

14:52.292 --> 14:53.414
I should have brought him in.

14:53.474 --> 15:01.546
We're not sure, but in verse 12, now they bring him in and he's described as being ready with beautiful eyes, enhance him in appearance.

15:02.087 --> 15:06.834
And the Lord says, arise, anoint him, for this is he.

15:07.810 --> 15:09.873
He's called ready, which means reddish.

15:11.335 --> 15:12.757
And reddish can mean one of two things.

15:12.957 --> 15:20.827
One is it could be he had red hair, though red hair in a Middle Eastern culture, not very common, most likely referring to then his complexion.

15:21.348 --> 15:27.576
I just want you to envision you're a 10 or a 12 year old kid in Fresno in August.

15:28.417 --> 15:29.479
What does your skin look like?

15:29.539 --> 15:32.382
You're probably ready, just like this guy.

15:32.402 --> 15:35.186
But he's also called a handsome in appearance.

15:35.522 --> 15:39.127
In that word, handsome means pleasant or desirable.

15:39.488 --> 15:43.774
There is something about this young scoundrel that is fascinating.

15:44.374 --> 15:46.317
You will love him and you will hate him.

15:46.998 --> 15:51.785
You will be proud of him and you will be so embarrassed by him and everything in between.

15:52.325 --> 15:53.888
And it says that he has beautiful eyes.

15:53.908 --> 15:56.471
You know, the old adage, the eyes are the gateway to the soul.

15:56.932 --> 16:04.242
There is something about this young boy who grows into quite a young man that has a very special relationship with God.

16:04.578 --> 16:07.102
is a very special individual.

16:07.442 --> 16:17.157
And so in verse 13, now Samuel took the horn of oil, anointed him in the midst of his brothers, and the spirit of the Lord came upon him, mightily from that day forward.

16:17.317 --> 16:25.570
It's interesting to me that Samuel includes here by way of authorship that he's anointed in front of his brothers.

16:26.471 --> 16:33.362
I think it's interesting that his brothers have to serve his witnesses to David the runt of the litter being now anointed king.

16:33.442 --> 16:39.088
and that God affirms He's the choice, because the Spirit of God comes upon Him mightily from that day forward.

16:40.129 --> 16:50.641
And so David now is anointed here as this new king, and the Spirit of the Lord coming upon Him begins to show you the uniqueness of relationship that David will have with our God.

16:51.362 --> 16:59.051
So if you read your Psalms, by the way, the book of Psalms, David is going to be attributed by way of authorship to over 70 of the Psalms.

16:59.832 --> 17:02.034
And so his heart for God is

17:02.242 --> 17:02.843
Incredible.

17:02.883 --> 17:08.569
And the thing I appreciate about David, and we'll get into this in a couple of weeks, David doesn't always make good decisions.

17:08.629 --> 17:12.613
I mean, if you think he's a man after God's own heart, because he always does the right thing, he does not.

17:13.314 --> 17:13.955
He does not.

17:14.435 --> 17:27.570
But what's interesting about David is when he doesn't, either he, by way of his own conscience and the work of the Spirit of God in his life, or by others who speak into his life and say, hey, what you did wasn't right, is very quick to repent.

17:28.002 --> 17:32.987
very quick to confess, very quick to seek God even in his brokenness.

17:33.368 --> 17:36.231
And I think in some ways that's what makes him a man after God's own heart.

17:36.632 --> 17:38.874
But I want you to listen by way of David writing the Psalms.

17:38.894 --> 17:45.862
I want you to listen now to some of the heart for God that comes out of David, this little shepherd king.

17:46.122 --> 17:49.205
Maybe you're familiar with Psalm 23, written by this boy.

17:49.926 --> 17:51.488
He says, the Lord is my shepherd.

17:52.589 --> 17:53.350
I shall not want.

17:54.011 --> 17:55.773
He makes me lie down in green pastures.

17:55.813 --> 17:57.074
He leads me beside

17:57.186 --> 17:59.449
Quiet waters, he restores my soul.

17:59.469 --> 18:03.975
He guides me in paths of righteousness for his namesake.

18:04.536 --> 18:12.026
And even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil for you or with me, your rod and your staff, they comfort me.

18:12.487 --> 18:15.892
You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies.

18:15.932 --> 18:19.016
You anoint my head with oil, my cup overflows.

18:19.857 --> 18:26.386
Surely goodness and loving kindness will follow me all the days of my life, and I will dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

18:26.850 --> 18:27.431
Not beautiful.

18:28.392 --> 18:29.874
He also wrote Psalm 13.

18:30.735 --> 18:34.941
Psalm 13, tell me if you've ever experienced the rawness of this emotion.

18:35.582 --> 18:38.486
He says, how long, O Lord, will you forget me forever?

18:39.728 --> 18:41.610
How long will you hide your face from me?

18:42.491 --> 18:44.815
How long will I take counsel in my soul?

18:45.616 --> 18:51.023
Having sorrow in my heart all the day, how long will my enemy be exalted over me?

18:51.604 --> 18:53.947
Consider and answer me, O Lord my God.

18:54.888 --> 18:56.050
Enlighten my eyes.

18:56.162 --> 18:57.924
Or I will sleep the sleep of death.

18:58.585 --> 19:00.488
And my enemy will say, I have overcome him.

19:01.049 --> 19:03.692
And my adversaries will rejoice when I am shaken.

19:04.594 --> 19:08.539
But I have trusted in your loving kindness.

19:09.300 --> 19:11.463
My heart shall rejoice in your salvation.

19:12.064 --> 19:15.769
I will sing to the Lord, because he has dealt bountifully with me.

19:15.989 --> 19:17.452
Have you ever had a moment like that?

19:17.992 --> 19:19.935
Or are you just like, how long?

19:20.816 --> 19:25.042
Like, Lord, do you see what's happening here?

19:25.154 --> 19:26.858
Are you going to show up in this moment?

19:26.878 --> 19:29.042
Because I'm literally, I think I'm going to die.

19:30.225 --> 19:32.008
I can't process this.

19:32.509 --> 19:33.271
I can't handle it.

19:33.291 --> 19:34.193
Have you ever felt like that?

19:35.095 --> 19:39.624
What I love about that passage is in verse five, he says, but I have trusted in your loving kindness.

19:40.065 --> 19:42.110
The word loving kindness is the Hebrew word, hessid.

19:42.130 --> 19:46.098
It means God's unconditional covenantal, unchanged, never-ending love.

19:47.074 --> 19:48.837
So I have trusted in your loving kindness.

19:49.197 --> 19:55.227
The pivot happens where he shifts from how long to, but I have trusted, but the circumstances never change.

19:56.669 --> 19:57.470
There's no relief.

19:58.151 --> 19:59.713
It's not like he cries out, how long?

19:59.774 --> 20:04.341
And God's like, oh my bad, takes the circumstance away and he says, okay, I'll worship you now.

20:04.441 --> 20:06.143
No, God never intervenes.

20:07.325 --> 20:08.968
David cries out in raw emotion.

20:10.330 --> 20:12.693
God doesn't remove the issue.

20:13.475 --> 20:15.698
And David catches himself and says, okay,

20:16.386 --> 20:17.828
I'm kind of whining a little bit here.

20:18.488 --> 20:19.990
I've trusted in your loving kindness.

20:20.090 --> 20:24.034
I know who you are, and it's unchanging, and so therefore I can worship.

20:24.054 --> 20:24.735
Isn't that beautiful?

20:24.775 --> 20:27.939
This is the heart of David now, the Shepherd King.

20:28.239 --> 20:35.247
What I'd like to do in the time that we have remaining, is just bring a couple of observations here from this text and just some things to think about.

20:36.148 --> 20:43.716
One's gonna be a little bit more theological, the other a little bit more location oriented, the other a little bit more generationally oriented.

20:43.736 --> 20:45.298
Let's talk about the theological one.

20:45.538 --> 20:51.665
It's interesting to me and worth noting in this text of what really matters to God, because I think it's applicable even today.

20:52.106 --> 20:56.591
What really matters to God is not what's happening on the outside, it's what's happening on the inside.

20:57.172 --> 21:03.640
So the eyes of the Lord moving to and fro throughout the earth that He may strongly support those whose hearts are completely his.

21:04.020 --> 21:06.704
But if that's indeed true, which it is, we have a problem.

21:07.404 --> 21:13.091
And the problem is your heart, my heart, is deceitfully wicked beyond repair.

21:14.253 --> 21:15.314
It is,

21:15.554 --> 21:17.116
bound to wickedness.

21:17.436 --> 21:19.258
It is fully depraved.

21:19.538 --> 21:22.281
There is no hope in my heart.

21:22.341 --> 21:43.922
In fact, Jesus is going to say of our hearts that from within the heart of men and women, proceed now, evil thoughts, fornications, thefts, murders, adultries, deeds of coveting, wickedness, as well as deceit, sensuality, envy, slander, pride, foolishness,

21:44.418 --> 21:49.045
all these evil things proceed from within and defile us.

21:49.245 --> 21:57.478
What's interesting about that is it means we don't have to find external things to make us do awful things.

21:58.159 --> 21:59.000
We don't need any help.

22:00.062 --> 22:01.304
We're actually bent that way.

22:02.085 --> 22:10.578
And if we're honest, that's the state of our heart, which means if you're here today and you have never trusted in Jesus Christ,

22:11.010 --> 22:16.817
The solution to a heart that is bent towards wickedness is not to be a better person.

22:18.039 --> 22:19.040
That's a fool's errand.

22:19.481 --> 22:25.088
There is no such thing as a person who on their own is good enough to interact with a holy God.

22:25.108 --> 22:25.989
That's not the solution.

22:26.289 --> 22:28.812
The solution is not to fix yourself.

22:28.832 --> 22:30.294
It's not to modify behavior.

22:30.795 --> 22:32.337
It's not to clean up your language.

22:32.377 --> 22:33.458
It's not to try to get sober.

22:33.478 --> 22:34.580
It's not to do any of those things.

22:35.000 --> 22:36.562
All of those things, as we have said,

22:36.866 --> 22:40.190
Repeatedly at this place are an overflow of the work of the gospel.

22:40.751 --> 22:50.683
In fact, the beauty of this thing called the gospel, the word gospel means good news, is that even while you were dead in your transgressions and sins, he made you alive together with Christ.

22:51.304 --> 22:55.069
That even when you were dead, God saved you.

22:55.589 --> 23:02.418
In fact, Titus 3.5 says that he saves us not on the base of deeds that we have done in righteousness, but according to his mercy,

23:02.978 --> 23:05.282
by the washing of regeneration and renewing of the Holy Spirit.

23:05.582 --> 23:09.187
That when you embrace the gospel, it's not just that your heart gets an upgrade.

23:10.109 --> 23:11.671
It's a full reinstall.

23:11.791 --> 23:20.224
It's a full renovation that God takes a heart of stone like Ezekiel 36 says and puts in us a heart of flesh.

23:20.565 --> 23:25.332
If anyone is in Christ, we're actually new creatures, old things pass away, new things have come.

23:25.713 --> 23:27.095
It's completely different.

23:28.177 --> 23:31.762
Having been justified by faith, we have peace with God.

23:32.354 --> 23:34.737
So what happens is theological, it's called imputation.

23:35.217 --> 23:38.541
This is what makes the gospel so unique versus being religious.

23:39.162 --> 23:42.706
Being religious would say every day and every way I get a little better and better.

23:43.027 --> 23:43.948
Good luck with that.

23:44.008 --> 23:46.331
No, this is full reset.

23:46.351 --> 23:49.054
Because when you place your faith in Jesus Christ, it's imputation.

23:49.555 --> 23:55.762
Imputation is when what was in your account is credited to another and what was in their account is credited to yours.

23:55.802 --> 23:57.804
That's the technical definition.

23:57.844 --> 23:59.186
Just by way of illustration.

23:59.394 --> 24:02.439
How many of you by chance have raised a college student?

24:02.579 --> 24:03.841
Raise your hand.

24:03.861 --> 24:08.549
Okay, to the rowdy's who are watching this in the PM, it's not your fault, it's a season of life thing.

24:08.569 --> 24:12.856
But there will probably come a time where you as a parent are gonna get the phone call.

24:13.557 --> 24:26.098
Mom, dad, I've got a problem, I've got, I don't know, a flat tire or whatever, but I work at the local coffee shop and pulling shots, you know, at a coffee shop is not gonna pay me enough money to fix my, I need your help.

24:27.042 --> 24:28.784
And so can you put some money in my account?

24:28.824 --> 24:31.366
Now you're going to log on to whatever banking app you use or whatnot.

24:31.667 --> 24:41.176
And you're going to take the money that you worked to earn and you out of love for your child, whether they deserve it or not, you're going to give that to them and you're going to transfer it to their account.

24:41.496 --> 24:45.640
They're going to be in the tire shop watching their account because they're negative balance already.

24:46.141 --> 24:49.584
And they're watching their account and then sure enough, boom, here comes the money.

24:49.944 --> 24:50.665
They didn't earn it.

24:50.745 --> 24:54.329
They don't deserve it, but they're going to tell that tire shop owner, here's the money.

24:54.389 --> 24:55.730
Now I can get my tires.

24:56.034 --> 24:56.955
Now, was it theirs?

24:57.135 --> 24:57.456
No!

24:58.177 --> 24:58.938
Do they have the money?

24:59.278 --> 24:59.578
No!

24:59.939 --> 25:00.920
How can they buy the tax?

25:00.960 --> 25:06.487
Because you buy your grace imputed to their account, that which they didn't earn or deserve.

25:06.907 --> 25:07.949
That is the work of the gospel.

25:09.030 --> 25:14.977
The work of the gospel is when we receive Jesus Christ as our Savior, He gives us His righteousness.

25:14.997 --> 25:19.683
So the Father doesn't see you and say, you should be a little bit better than you are right now.

25:20.364 --> 25:21.906
That's what you say to you.

25:22.018 --> 25:25.483
When you receive Jesus Christ, His righteousness is yours.

25:25.764 --> 25:29.590
Therefore the Father who is holy sees you, who are holy.

25:29.650 --> 25:32.734
Now, are you practically holy?

25:32.915 --> 25:34.337
Well, not usually.

25:35.218 --> 25:36.841
But are you positionally holy?

25:37.141 --> 25:39.284
Yes, that's the gospel.

25:39.725 --> 25:42.289
Which is why we say something has to happen.

25:43.190 --> 25:45.875
You have to place your faith in Jesus Christ.

25:46.495 --> 25:48.178
You don't just start coming to church.

25:48.610 --> 25:50.232
It's not just about being baptized.

25:50.332 --> 25:52.015
It's not just about enjoying communion.

25:52.315 --> 25:53.797
Those are all wonderful things.

25:54.358 --> 25:56.060
Something has to happen.

25:56.681 --> 25:59.585
And when it does, your heart is made new.

26:00.406 --> 26:03.490
But not only does something need to happen.

26:04.151 --> 26:08.337
Once it does, voice something needs to continue to happen.

26:08.357 --> 26:12.222
We need to fix our eyes on Jesus, the author and perfecter of our faith.

26:12.302 --> 26:15.186
We need to continue to seek the things of God.

26:16.322 --> 26:20.167
keeping our minds focused on Christ, our hearts moving towards Christ.

26:20.187 --> 26:21.910
Christianity is not a one and done.

26:22.150 --> 26:27.478
Like back in 1984, I trusted Christ at a youth camp or whatever.

26:28.059 --> 26:33.647
Back when I was in high school, I went to Hume Lake, I heard a speaker, I came forward on decision night.

26:33.707 --> 26:35.089
Okay, all that's fine.

26:35.810 --> 26:41.778
But that's the beginning of a journey, a lifelong journey of constant formation of our hearts.

26:42.210 --> 26:53.565
where we are continually opening to the Lord, spending time in His Word, reading the Bible, letting it read us, changing the way we live, living in pursuit of Christ, not in hopes of salvation.

26:53.605 --> 26:56.990
You're already saved in response to salvation.

26:57.771 --> 27:06.943
Because of what He's done for us, how could we not orient our life towards a continued pursuit of the God who so loved us that He saved us?

27:07.804 --> 27:09.587
And so, man sees the outside.

27:10.508 --> 27:12.050
Thankfully, God sees the heart.

27:12.450 --> 27:14.072
Let's talk about situationally now.

27:15.153 --> 27:21.220
When David was out shepherding sheep, I just wonder if he felt overlooked.

27:21.240 --> 27:26.146
Now, truth be known, he may not have even known Jesse was in town, or excuse me, Samuel was in town.

27:26.446 --> 27:27.387
He may not have even known.

27:27.728 --> 27:29.009
He's just out shepherding sheep.

27:29.029 --> 27:33.354
I mean, it's not like he's getting a text message out in the field, okay?

27:33.554 --> 27:34.936
So maybe he doesn't even know.

27:35.777 --> 27:40.082
But when the messenger comes out and says, hey, Samuel, the prophet's in town,

27:40.386 --> 27:43.210
He's gonna anoint one of Jesse's sons to be king.

27:43.690 --> 27:44.972
It wasn't the other seven.

27:48.517 --> 27:49.398
So that leaves you.

27:50.760 --> 27:54.225
You wonder if he felt overlooked, disregarded.

27:55.426 --> 27:57.930
You wonder if he felt forgotten.

27:57.950 --> 27:59.932
Have you ever felt that?

27:59.952 --> 28:01.254
So here's the interesting thing.

28:01.855 --> 28:05.500
Wherever you are, you are there with a purpose.

28:06.581 --> 28:10.226
So here's David out there and I would bet in the flesh

28:10.658 --> 28:11.720
He probably felt that.

28:12.581 --> 28:13.663
Like, Lord, do you see?

28:13.723 --> 28:16.026
Are you aware?

28:16.066 --> 28:18.069
Are you able?

28:19.031 --> 28:19.992
Are you involved?

28:21.014 --> 28:23.958
Because I'm out here smelling like a sheep.

28:26.362 --> 28:27.524
And have you forgotten about me?

28:27.844 --> 28:29.847
And the answer to that, of course, is no.

28:30.708 --> 28:31.830
Your God does see you.

28:32.211 --> 28:33.673
He is able.

28:33.713 --> 28:34.414
He is aware.

28:34.494 --> 28:35.836
He is involved.

28:36.056 --> 28:39.762
What was happening, though, while he was out there shepherding sheep?

28:40.642 --> 28:46.849
Well, his heart was learning to trust God who was just enough for him out there in the wilderness.

28:47.630 --> 28:52.835
While he's out there shepherding sheep, he's learning how to do with sheep, which is not an easy thing to do.

28:53.456 --> 28:56.800
Preparing him for dealing with people, which is not an easy thing to do.

28:57.901 --> 28:59.763
While he's out there, he's learning how to play his guitar.

29:00.804 --> 29:05.970
He's learning how to write poetry, which your Psalms are really a hymnal in your Bible.

29:06.178 --> 29:08.742
He's learning how to express worship to God.

29:08.762 --> 29:11.306
He's writing worship tunes out there in the wilderness.

29:11.547 --> 29:13.770
He's also getting pretty good with this little slingshot.

29:15.413 --> 29:20.761
So as he's shepherding sheep and the lions and bears are coming, he's defending his sheep.

29:20.782 --> 29:28.774
He's growing his skillset that in the moment, probably seemed like that was the end destination of that skillset until chapter 17.

29:30.016 --> 29:33.522
When the goliath, the giant goliath comes down,

29:34.082 --> 29:41.050
into the valley of Elon, cries out for someone who's willing to defend the reputation of your God, whoever he is.

29:41.090 --> 29:45.215
And so here comes David, slingshot in hand, having been trained out in the wilderness.

29:45.235 --> 29:49.020
So look, I don't know where God has you, and I don't know how you feel about that.

29:50.001 --> 29:56.869
But I just want you to know, if you feel forgotten, if you feel overlooked, if you feel disregarded, your God sees you.

29:58.371 --> 29:59.533
He knows every hair on your head.

30:00.093 --> 30:00.934
Your God is able.

30:01.815 --> 30:04.018
He is aware, and he is involved.

30:04.162 --> 30:07.025
And right now, it may not make sense to you.

30:07.906 --> 30:19.637
Right now, you may think, yeah, I'm not sure that that's true, because if you knew what I was going through right now, and I don't know, and I would imagine if you can relate to this illustration, it's got to be really, really difficult.

30:20.197 --> 30:26.683
But can I remind you that in the difficulty, God is doing something in you that He would never do if you were already in the palace?

30:27.384 --> 30:30.627
Third is going to be more season of life oriented.

30:31.248 --> 30:33.650
I'm fascinated by Samuel's story.

30:34.082 --> 30:36.665
Now we're gonna kind of turn the page on Samuel too.

30:36.705 --> 30:53.165
He shows up in our story, but he's not the main focal point, but his story arc, if you're into literature, his story arc is fascinating because his mom prays for a kid and God finally provides a child and she says, Lord, if you give me a child, this is Hannah.

30:53.826 --> 30:56.549
If you give me a child, I will give him to you.

30:57.611 --> 31:00.434
Now you and I say that, we're like, I commit my kid to you.

31:00.474 --> 31:03.698
Now he's mine, but I commit him to you kind of mine.

31:04.866 --> 31:11.556
She literally drops him off at the tabernacle to Eli the priest and says, I made a commitment to God.

31:12.257 --> 31:13.639
There's my three year old child.

31:14.421 --> 31:18.667
Now you can debate the moral implications of that and what kind of maternal instinct that is.

31:18.727 --> 31:19.468
Here's what I want you to know.

31:19.789 --> 31:23.635
This woman prayed to God for a son and said, if you give me a son, I'll give him to you.

31:23.655 --> 31:25.117
God gave her a son, she kept her word.

31:25.698 --> 31:30.004
And so now Samuel grows up in the temple as a three year old kid.

31:30.766 --> 31:33.650
As a child,

31:34.146 --> 31:39.975
He has a relationship with God where God calls his name and he says, speak, Lord, your servant is listening.

31:40.215 --> 31:41.116
That's incredible.

31:41.897 --> 31:48.788
He's anointed now as the prophet over the entire region as a young adult, as a middle-aged man.

31:48.848 --> 31:50.831
He's gonna call the people back to repentance.

31:51.612 --> 31:58.462
He's the guy who as a older man is gonna anoint Saul King, oops, anoint David King.

31:58.502 --> 32:04.050
He's the guy who, by the way, as an older man later in his life.

32:04.546 --> 32:18.143
in his 70s, in his 80s, or maybe in his 90s, is still learning and growing and being faithful to the Lord, trusting God with his future and fully engaged in the kingdom.

32:18.163 --> 32:27.634
Now, that's a different perspective, because we tend to think like, okay, we're kids, who cares, okay, we get older, okay now, what we say kind of matters, and then maybe

32:27.810 --> 32:31.754
Maybe we're in our 20s and 30s, maybe we have an opinion about stuff, but we don't have any gray hair yet.

32:31.794 --> 32:32.635
So do we really know?

32:32.655 --> 32:34.818
And then maybe you've earned some gray hair or lost some hair.

32:34.898 --> 32:38.081
And so now you've got something to say, which is great.

32:38.121 --> 32:40.564
And then you finally get older.

32:41.165 --> 32:44.148
And then it's time after making your hay to retire.

32:46.070 --> 32:48.753
And then we all move to Florida.

32:50.375 --> 32:51.536
We live on a golf course.

32:53.118 --> 32:54.359
And we learn to play bridge.

32:54.579 --> 32:56.882
OK, is that really?

32:57.122 --> 32:58.404
Is that really what God says?

32:59.065 --> 33:03.853
Or is it possible that Samuel's story arc has a model for us that he's faithful as a child?

33:04.534 --> 33:05.917
He's faithful as a student.

33:06.438 --> 33:07.980
And he's faithful as a young adult.

33:08.301 --> 33:10.544
And he's faithful as a middle-aged man.

33:10.745 --> 33:12.568
And he's faithful as an older man.

33:12.648 --> 33:14.651
And he's faithful as an elderly man.

33:14.952 --> 33:21.903
And from the earliest of ages, all the way to his death, his focus is kingdom, kingdom, kingdom.

33:22.164 --> 33:23.506
Now, it looked different.

33:24.898 --> 33:29.604
I mean, you're going to reach an age, if you haven't already, where you will groan getting off of your own couch.

33:31.787 --> 33:34.031
Some of you are too young to know what that means, okay?

33:35.012 --> 33:36.854
You'll get up in your knees, oh, pop.

33:36.915 --> 33:38.497
And people are like, what, fireworks?

33:38.637 --> 33:39.478
Like, no, it's just my knees.

33:40.620 --> 33:48.470
But there is an opportunity that we have to follow the story arc of Samuel and say, look, we could be faithful to God in every season of our life.

33:48.491 --> 33:53.938
And by the way, there will be no more joy in life that you can find than to do just that.

33:54.434 --> 34:14.995
and whether you're a young child, whether you're a student, whether you're a young adult, whether you're in your career, young married, whether you're older, whether you're elderly, whatever season of life you're in, what would it look like for you to seek first his kingdom and his righteousness, knowing that all these things will be added to you as well.

34:15.075 --> 34:15.295
Amen?

34:16.356 --> 34:17.357
Let's pray together.

34:17.377 --> 34:22.322
Father, I'm thankful for this section of Scripture that reminds us of who you are

34:22.850 --> 34:25.214
in what you've invited us, Lord, to be about.

34:25.314 --> 34:27.477
You see a different metric.

34:28.599 --> 34:29.560
Man sees the outside.

34:29.580 --> 34:30.382
You see the heart.

34:31.083 --> 34:33.166
So Lord, could our hearts be presented to you?

34:34.007 --> 34:37.232
Could we be faithful in whatever location you've placed us in?

34:37.873 --> 34:45.645
And could we be focused on your kingdom, regardless of what season of life we're in, that God, our focus would always be on the things of God.

34:45.705 --> 34:51.474
So thank you for this text that challenges and encourages us to think maybe differently

34:51.682 --> 34:56.237
about what you value and therefore what should be important to us as well.

34:56.257 --> 34:59.246
For again, man sees the outside, but you see the heart.

34:59.266 --> 35:01.714
So bless us, I pray in Jesus' name, amen.

